## Language Modeling

$$V$$
:   some (finite) vocabulary
$$V^\dagger$$
:   (infinite) set of sentences
$$p$$
:   $$p$$ is a function that satisfies
> $$\sum_{x\in V^\dagger}p(x) = 1$$, where $$p(x)\ge 0$$ for all $$x \in V^\dagger$$

## Markov Processes

Assume that: for any $$i \in {2...n}$$, for any $$x_1...x_i$$,
> $$P(X_i=x_i|X_1=x_1...X_{i-1}=x_{i-1}) = P(X_i=x_i|X_{i-1}=x_{i-1})$$

